# O-Walkie Project Memory

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Go relay server (`backend/cmd/relay/main.go`), WebSocket control + UDP audio data.
- Android client: Kotlin, foreground `WalkieService`, Opus via `kopus`, Gradle Kotlin DSL.
- Windows client: C++ wxWidgets (`windows-client-cpp`), Boost.Beast, **miniaudio** (vendored), Opus (legacy C# WPF removed).
- Audio protocol: Opus mono, server handshake with protocol/version/audio params.

## Current Task
- Active development is ongoing for both clients in equal priority: Android and Windows (`windows-client-cpp`).
- Feature policy: all new user-facing or protocol-impacting functionality must be implemented in both clients with parity unless explicitly scoped otherwise.
- Windows release baseline includes: GUI subsystem app (`owalkie-desktop.exe`), auto-reconnect, profiles/settings persistence, signaling flow parity (`Roger` on PTT release, manual `Call`), local signal playback, global keyboard PTT hotkey, and release packaging to `build/dist`.
- Legacy `windows-client` (WPF/.NET) is removed from repository and no longer participates in feature parity.
- Android and Windows are both in active feature + reliability iteration, with parity checks required before release.

## Recent Key Changes
- Backend: hardened channel mixer runtime against UDP/audio generation crashes — added panic recovery with stack trace, emergency mixer loop restart with backoff, and codec/repeater state reinitialization after failure so relay process stays alive under runtime faults.
- Backend: mixer emergency restarts now expose a lifetime counter per channel and log `ALERT` when ≥5 restarts occur within 1 minute (throttled to once per 30s per channel) for operator visibility.
- Backend: UDP keepalive punch now triggers unicast resend of the last mixed frame to that client (after ACK), with a 500ms catch-up age window so joiners mid-transmission get audio immediately even when `udp_hello` races or NAT path differs from WS peer IP.
- Windows (`windows-client-cpp`): incoming stream volume slider 0–200% (persisted as `rx_volume_percent` in `audio.json`, matches Android `RxVolumeStore`); connection fields use read-only editing while session active instead of hiding/disabled grey blocks; repeater checkbox live-toggles `repeater_mode` over WS when connected; relay teardown uses `cancel()` + non-throwing close/read/write to avoid Beast `!impl.wr_close` asserts and UI freezes on disconnect.
- Android + Windows: keepalive stage-1 tuning for faster idle recovery — reduced UDP keepalive lost-timeout and slightly faster RTX cadence to avoid long post-silence recovery windows (~30s symptom).
- Protocol/transport: added explicit UDP keepalive ACK (`signal=254, seq=0, empty opus`) in backend relay for client keepalive punches (`signal=255, seq=0`), enabling ACK-aware client keepalive state machine.
- Android: keepalive loop now uses TeamTalk-like interval/RTX/lost-timeout behavior (`interval`, `RTX`, `connection-lost`) with pending-ACK tracking; incoming UDP keepalive ACK clears pending state and prevents idle pinhole decay.
- Android: recovery stabilization pass in `WalkieService` — increased foreground UDP recv timeout (`300ms -> 1000ms`), added timeout-burst debounce before UDP recovery, and serialized WS reconnect + UDP socket recreate through shared recovery mutex to avoid overlapping network recovery coroutines.
- Windows: added settings toggle for microphone level progress bar (`show_mic_level_indicator` in `audio.json`); default is `off`, hidden indicator does not update and resets to zero.
- Windows: global PTT key assignment now uses a dedicated modal capture dialog that supports modifier combos (`Ctrl`/`Alt`/`Shift` + key); combo display/persistence added via `ptt_hotkey_mods`, `Clear` behavior preserved.
- Windows: connection management UI terminology and form were aligned closer to Android flow: `Profiles` renamed to `Connections`, inline `Connection name` field added to the main form, and save/new/delete actions remain directly accessible.
- Windows: Android-style TX collision "vibration" parity added as desktop tone pattern emulation (`100 Hz` pulses with Android timing pattern `35/55/35/55/35 ms`) triggered on incoming-audio-while-TX burst detection with cooldown.
- Windows: aligned connection UX tones with Android: manual connect start `{932.33, 1174.66, 1396.91, 1864.66}`, manual disconnect reverse sequence, handshake-success connected tone `{1400Hz 40ms, pause 50ms, 1700Hz 50ms}`, plus explicit connection error tone on connect failure and link loss.
- Windows: moved connected sound trigger from raw WS connect state to post-`welcome` handling (after negotiated parameters are applied), matching "successful handshake + init" semantics.
- Android: added TX single-run guard in `WalkieService` (`txLoopRunning` CAS) to prevent duplicate capture/transmit coroutine starts during reconnect/race conditions under heavy PTT activity.
- Android: updated UI connection tones: manual connect start now plays `{932.33, 1174.66, 1396.91, 1864.66}` sequence, manual disconnect/reconnect step uses reverse sequence, and successful handshake/parameter init "connected" tone is now `{1400Hz 40ms, pause 50ms, 1700Hz 50ms}`.
- Android: connection error tone now plays for protocol incompatibility, failed connect attempts, and unexpected link loss while user-requested connection remains active.
- Windows: switched desktop build to GUI subsystem (`WIN32`) so release executable runs without background console window.
- Windows: legacy `windows-client` WPF project removed and committed as retired after migration to C++ desktop client.
- Windows: finalized release-facing naming (window title `O-Walkie Desktop`, output `owalkie-desktop.exe`), added build/debug ignores in `.gitignore`, and treated desktop target as production release path.
- Windows: local UI signals (`PTT press/release`, `Roger`, `Call`, `Connected`) now play through separate one-shot high-quality playback path resampled to `44100 Hz`, decoupled from narrowband relay stream rate.
- Windows: desktop client now looks up Android-matched UI sounds in `<exe>/sounds` (`selfpttup_002`, `selfttdown_002`; optional `.wav`) with generated fallback if missing; build post-step copies files from `android/app/src/main/res/raw` into `build/sounds` and `build/dist/sounds`.
- Windows: added Android-like RX resume holdoff after TX/call/roger signaling in desktop audio path; incoming audio is temporarily suppressed during holdoff to avoid immediate post-TX buffer clashes.
- Windows: added local UI signals in desktop client for PTT press and successful connect (generated tones), aligned with Android-side UX behavior.
- Windows: added configurable global keyboard PTT hotkey (`down` = start TX, `up` = stop TX) via low-level global key hook; hotkey selection/clear moved into desktop settings dialog and persisted in `audio.json` (`ptt_hotkey_vkey`).
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` added settings dialog and moved audio device selection from main screen; added signal pattern selection (`Roger`/`Call`) and persisted selected IDs in `audio.json`.
- Windows: signal generation now also plays locally in desktop client (`Roger` on PTT release, `Call` on button), while still streaming Opus signal frames to relay and finalizing with TX EOF.
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` added generated signal streaming path (PCM -> Opus -> UDP -> TX EOF); `Roger` now triggers on PTT release (Android-like flow), while `Call` remains manual button-triggered.
- Android: fixed crash on network handoff (`StackOverflowError`) by breaking recursive recovery loop between `recreateUdpSocket()` and `sendUdpKeepalivePacket()`; keepalive send from recreate path now skips nested recovery call.
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` `RelayClient::Connect` — UDP remote endpoint берётся из `tcp::socket::remote_endpoint()` (тот же адрес, что и WS), сокет UDP открывается v4/v6 в соответствии; убран `make_address(host)` на этапе UDP (исправление WSAEINVAL для имён вроде `localhost`).
- Android: fixed potential Activity resume ANR by moving UDP socket timeout policy update (`soTimeout`) off the service main thread to `Dispatchers.IO`.
- Windows: C++ wxWidgets client persists last connection fields to `%AppData%`-style user data dir as `connection.json` (host/ports/channel/repeater); app/vendor display names set for stable config path.
- Windows: `windows-client-cpp` — miniaudio вместо PortAudio; выбор устройств ввода/вывода, сохранение индексов в `connection.json`; POST_BUILD кладёт exe и UCRT64 DLL в `build/dist/` (`scripts/bundle-ucrt64-deps.sh`, кэш `OWALKIE_MSYS_ROOT`).
- Windows client: reduced UDP keepalive aggressiveness to `5s` with ±15% jitter to lower synchronized keepalive bursts while preserving simple desktop networking behavior.
- Android: tuned background idle battery mode further — `UDP_BG_KEEPALIVE_IDLE_INTERVAL_SEC=50`, `UDP_RECV_TIMEOUT_BACKGROUND_MS=10000`, cached signal-strength polling in background (max once per 50s), immediate keepalive mode switch on app focus change.
- Android: reduce background battery use (softer UDP keepalive when app not in focus, longer RX socket timeout in background), bind UDP `DatagramSocket` to `ConnectivityManager` active `Network` after handoffs, queue UDP socket recreation until end of TX/call/roger, reset Opus on new `sessionId` and fix playback loop race on reconnect.
- Implemented server-side configurable Opus parameters (bitrate/complexity/FEC/DTX/application) and handshake propagation.
- Added and refined idle squelch shot scheduler on server:
  - timer random `10..squelch_shots` seconds (when idle),
  - shot duration random `tail_min_ms..tail_max_ms`,
  - 1s silence before and after shot.
- Changed relay startup config behavior:
  - default uses `./config.json`,
  - optional config path via first CLI argument.
- Removed Android Accessibility service path and background hardware PTT flow:
  - deleted `PttAccessibilityService`,
  - removed manifest/xml declarations and related strings/UI/settings logic.

